FBIS3-23109 "jptot010__l94072" JPRS-TOT-94-010-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Terrorism FOUO 10 March 1994 NEAR EAST/SOUTH ASIA EGYPT German Tourist on Nile Cruise Shot by Muslim Militants IG Reiterates Threat on Foreigners NC0403125594 Paris AFP in English 1151 GMT 4 Mar 94 NC0403125594 Paris AFP Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Asyut, Egypt, March 4 (AFP)--Muslim militants shot and seriously wounded a German tourist Friday when they opened fire on a Nile cruise boat in southern Egypt, security sources said. The tourist was taken to a hospital in the southern city of Asyut after he was shot while on the cruise near Abu Tij, some 30 kilometres (18 miles) south of here, the sources said. The victim was not named. There was no confirmation of the incident from the Interior Ministry or the German Embassy in Cairo. [passage omitted]
